## Education

The future, or at least the next generation, is shaped within these walls.

### Public schools

The administrative nerve center for [Cumberland County Schools](/Cumberland_County_Schools) is conveniently situated in Fayetteville. This rather extensive school system oversees a total of 87 educational institutions: 53 elementary schools, 16 middle schools, 15 high schools, and 9 Alternative and Specialty schools. The latter category includes 1 year-round classical academy, 1 evening academy, 1 web academy, and 2 specialized schools, demonstrating a rather diverse approach to pedagogy. [Cumberland County Schools](/Cumberland_County_Schools) proudly holds the distinction of being the fourth-largest school system in the state and the 78th-largest in the entire country. A rather significant bureaucratic undertaking, to be sure.

[Cumberland County Schools](/Cumberland_County_Schools) is primarily responsible for educating students from Pre-Kindergarten through 12th grade across most areas of Fayetteville. However, for students residing on [Fort Bragg](/Fort_Bragg), the [Department of Defense Education Activity](/Department_of_Defense_Education_Activity) (DoDEA) operates public schools specifically for grades PK-8. Once these students reach high school, they transition to local public schools within their respective counties, a somewhat convoluted, yet functional, system.

#### High schools (grades 9–12)

*   [Cape Fear High School](/Cape_Fear_High_School) – Home to the School of Agricultural & Natural Sciences Academy (9–12), for those inclined towards the practicalities of the earth.
*   [Douglas Byrd High School](/Douglas_Byrd_High_School) – Featuring the Finance Academy & Ford Partnerships for Advanced Studies (9–12), preparing students for the relentless pursuit of capital.
*   [Ezekiel Ezra "E.E." Smith High School](/E.E._Smith_High_School) – Offers Academies of Math & Science and Fire Science (9–12), a rather eclectic combination of disciplines.
*   [Jack Britt High School](/Jack_Britt_High_School) – Known for its Academy of Integrated Systems of Technology and Applied Engineering (9–12), for those who prefer building to theorizing.
*   [Pine Forest High School](/Pine_Forest_High_School_(North_Carolina)) – Provides Academies of Emergency Medical Science & Information Technology (9–12), catering to both saving lives and managing data.
*   [Seventy-First High School](/Seventy-First_High_School) – Focuses on the School of Arts (9–12), for those who dare to express themselves.
*   [Terry Sanford High School](/Terry_Sanford_High_School) – Features the Global Studies Academy (9–12), presumably preparing students for a world that refuses to simplify.
*   [Westover High School](/Westover_High_School_(Fayetteville,_North_Carolina)) – Hosts Academies of Health and Engineering (9–12), a practical combination for a practical world.
