### Air transportation

[Fayetteville Regional Airport](/Fayetteville_Regional_Airport) serves as the city's primary aerial gateway, facilitating movement for those who prefer to traverse the skies. It is serviced by five regional carriers, which dutifully provide daily and seasonal passenger services to three major airline hubs scattered across the [United States](/United_States). An additional regional carrier, along with several fixed-base operators, offers further services for both passenger and general aviation operations, ensuring a steady stream of aerial activity. [Landmark Aviation](/Landmark_Aviation) also contributes to the airport's operational ecosystem, providing services for both passenger and general aviation traffic.

### Public transportation

The [Fayetteville Area System of Transit](/Fayetteville_Area_System_of_Transit) (FAST) is the city's primary provider of public transportation, diligently serving both the Fayetteville and [Spring Lake](/Spring_Lake,_North_Carolina) regions. Its network comprises ten bus routes and two shuttle routes, a rather comprehensive system for local transit. FAST operates a total of thirteen fixed bus routes within the city of Fayetteville itself, ensuring coverage across its urban expanse. Service hours extend from 5:45 am to 10:30 pm on weekdays, with a somewhat reduced schedule on Saturdays, and, rather predictably, no service on Sundays—a day of rest, even for public transport. The majority of these routes commence and conclude their journeys at the central Transfer Center, conveniently located at 147 Old Wilmington Road in Fayetteville. Additional transfer points are strategically placed at University Estates, [Cross Creek Mall](/Cross_Creek_Mall), the Veterans Administration Medical Center, the intersection of Bunce and Cliffdale Roads, and the Cape Fear Valley Medical Center, ensuring accessibility across key areas.

### Passenger rail

The historic [Atlantic Coast Line Railroad](/Atlantic_Coast_Line_Railroad) Station, a venerable structure dating back to 1911, continues to provide daily [Amtrak](/Amtrak) service. This rail connection offers both northbound and southbound routes, linking Fayetteville to various points along the sprawling [East Coast](/East_Coast). A testament to the enduring, if sometimes overlooked, efficiency of rail travel.

